The paper proposes a new model for classifying time series that allows the use of both shape and feature-based measures, which is a problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also evaluates the proposed idea on real-world datasets, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
